

Using ElasticSearch Flume integration

1. Build it using Maven:

    1.1 Install the Flume library into your local Maven repo (because it's not available in central)
        mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=com.cloudera -DartifactId=flume -Dversion=0.9.1-dev -Dclassifier=core -Dfile=flume-0.9.1-dev-core.jar -Dpackaging=jar


    1.2 Build elasticflume

    mvn package

2. Ensure your Flume installation has a copy of the elasticSearch jars. The below will work, a dirty hack though it may be:

    ln -s $ELASTICSEARCH_HOME/lib/*.jar $FLUME_HOME/lib

3. Now add the elasticflume jar into the classpath too:

    ln -s target/elasticflume*.jar $FLUME_HOME/lib/

4. Startup Flume Master, and Flume nodes.
